{"lemma":"بَلِيَّة","slug":"بَلِيَّة","root":"ب.ل.#","root_slug":"ب-ل-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ب-ل-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n3291","n3306","n3296"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A8%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plight, calamity, dire state"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"marble to play"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Italian bilia, biglia."},"ipa":["/ba.lij.ja/","/bil.ja/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n3291","headword_ar":"بِلْيَةٌ","root":"blw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see what next follows."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3306","headword_ar":"بِلْيَةٌ","root":"blY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliY~N","text_ar":"بَلِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliy~apN","text_ar":"بَلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blw","text_ar":"بلو"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n3296","headword_ar":"بَلِيَّةٌ","root":"blw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaA='N","text_ar":"بَلَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places.       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A she-camel that has her fore shank bound to her arm at the grave of her master, and is left without food until she dies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blw","text_ar":"بلو"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blY","text_ar":"بلى"},{"kind":"text","text":", and K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a mare,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beast of the equine kind,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"blw","text_ar":"بلو"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is bound at the grave of her master,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he being dead, and is left without food or water"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"until she dies"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and wastes away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for they used to say that her master would be raised from the dead upon her: (M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a she-camel which, in the Time of Ignorance, had her fore shank bound to her arm at the grave of her master, and was left without food or water until she died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for which was dug a pit, wherein she was left until she died:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for they used to assert that men would be raised from the dead riding upon the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaAyaA","text_ar":"بَلَايَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", [pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliy~apN","text_ar":"بَلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense above explained, (T, TA,)] or walking if their beasts whereon they rode were not bound, with the head turned backwards, at their graves: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cow,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"she-camel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, which, in the Time of Ignorance, they used to hamstring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughter, at the grave:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in a trad. (TA.) Suh says that this custom proves that, in the Time of Ignorance, they held the doctrine of the resurrection of the body: but they who held it were the fewer number. (TA.) It is said that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliy~apN","text_ar":"بَلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is originally ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubolaApN","text_ar":"مُبْلَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mubal~aApN","text_ar":"مُبَلَّاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Et-Tirimmáh says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"manaAzilu laA taraY AlA^anoSaAba fiyhaA\n                      \n                     \n                        walaA Hufara Almubal~aY lilomanuwni"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Places of abode in which thou wilt not see the stones,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other things, that have been set up to be worshipped, nor the pits of the beast left by the grave of the master to die"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; meaning places of abode of the people of El-Islám, exclusively of the pagans. (S.) IAar says that ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliY~N","text_ar":"بَلِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baliy~apN","text_ar":"بَلِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such as is wearied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"jaded, and emaciated, and dying."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","K","TA","S"]}]}}